{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/creation-of-information-graphic-animations-with-tableau-21cfc7660189", "time": 1683006700.1760561, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/creation-of-information-graphic-animations-with-tableau-21cfc7660189/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Creation of information graphic animations with Tableau | by Andreas St\u00f6ckl | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Creation of information graphic animations with Tableau", "description": "In my earlier article \u201cAnimated Information Graphics\u201d I dealt with how time-dependent data can be displayed as animations using \u201cPython\u201d and \u201cPlotly\u201d. In this article, I want to show how to create\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/animated-information-graphics-4531de620ce7", "anchor_text": "Animated Information Graphics", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "http://www.tableau.com", "anchor_text": "Tableau", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/publications-data/download-todays-data-geographic-distribution-covid-19-cases-worldwide", "anchor_text": "downloaded", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "https://public.tableau.com/", "anchor_text": "Tableau Public", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "http://www.stoeckl.ai/profil/", "anchor_text": "http://www.stoeckl.ai/profil/", "paragraph_index": 10}], "all_paragraphs": ["In my earlier article \u201cAnimated Information Graphics\u201d I dealt with how time-dependent data can be displayed as animations using \u201cPython\u201d and \u201cPlotly\u201d. In this article, I want to show how to create animations of information graphics with the new 2020 version of the software Tableau.", "For the examples I use data on COVID19 infections in the individual countries, which can be downloaded from the \u201cEuropean Centre for Disease Prevention and Control\u201d. You can follow the examples with the free version \u201cTableau Public\u201d.", "An animated version of bar charts, which enjoys great popularity on YouTube, are the so-called \u201cRacing Barcharts\u201d. Here, the animation is created by a sequence of individual bar charts that are sorted according to an order, and follow this order (\u201cThe Race\u201d) over time.", "The following example shows the development of the total number of COVID19 infections per country per 100,000 inhabitants. In each case, the top 15 countries worldwide from March 1. 2020, and only countries with more than one million inhabitants are considered.", "Instructions for creating such animations can be found, for example, at", "\u201cChoropleth Maps\u201d are representations of maps in which the individual countries are coloured according to a colour code. This colour code represents a numerical value. In our example, this is the number of infections measured per 100,000 inhabitants. If the map representations of the individual days are now joined together, an animation is obtained that shows not only the chronological course but also the geographical distribution of the infections.", "In the period under consideration (from March 2020), the centre of the spread of infections is located in Europe and North America. Towards the end of the time period shown (end of April), a spread in South America and Eastern Europe can be observed. However, a disadvantage of the Choropleth representation is that small countries with high populations are only slightly visible and large countries such as Russia, Canada and the USA are very dominant.", "An introduction to the creation of \u201cChoropleth Maps\u201d in Tableau can be found here:", "If you now place the data field for the day on the \u201cPage shelf\u201d in Tableau and switch on the animation function with the menu item \u201cFormat/Animations\u201d, you can easily obtain the desired animation. An individual adjustment of the colour scale then provides the desired appearance.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "University of Applied Sciences Upper Austria / School of Informatics, Communications and Media http://www.stoeckl.ai/profil/"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F21cfc7660189&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fcreation-of-information-graphic-animations-with-tableau-21cfc7660189&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fcreation-of-information-graphic-animations-with-tableau-21cfc7660189&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fcreation-of-information-graphic-animations-with-tableau-21cfc7660189&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fcreation-of-information-graphic-animations-with-tableau-21cfc7660189&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url":